title: Tigers win catfight against Cougars, 12 – 0
text:
Tigers win catfight against Cougars, 12 – 0 Posted on 23 October 2015 by KWBG 
Madrid fought its way into the playoffs with a win at Manson Northwest Webster Friday evening. After a scoreless first quarter, the Tigers’ Michael Santi had a 10-yard touchdown run in the second period. In the third quarter, Bryce Dean scampered in from the 3 yard line and that was it as Madrid clawed the Cougars, 12 – 0. With an overall record of 7 and 2, 4 and 2 in district play, the Tigers will host a first-round game Wednesday night. Leave a Reply You must be logged in to post a comment. Boone Municipal, IA
